News24 CorrespondentFILE (Screengrab) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Two men who were found in possession of stolen goods, including seven bibles, were rescued &ndash;&nbsp;and then arrested by police &ndash; after they were attacked by an angry mob in Kagiso, police said on Sunday. &ldquo;We received a complaint of two suspects that were in possession of suspected stolen property in block 5 Tshepisong West,&rdquo; said Captain Solomon Sibiya in a statement about the incident which took place on Friday afternoon. He said when police arrived on the scene they found a gathering of people from the area. &ldquo;Police noticed two unknown men lying on the ground and bleeding from injuries.&ldquo; Community members said the men had been breaking into homes and stealing various goods. When police searched the mens&rsquo; shack they found curtains, camera stands, a tablet and seven bibles. &ldquo;The two suspects were put under arrest after they failed to account for the property.&rdquo; The men will appear at the Kagiso Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Monday. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.